Oh, my goodness, you know what
we were just doing right now?

11:14.306 --> 11:15.710
Both: A "what if."

11:15.710 --> 11:18.745
Oh, well, I have what if
the Hulk had killed Wolverine?

11:18.797 --> 11:21.998
What if Wolverine had killed the Hulk?

11:22.050 --> 11:24.884
And what if Wolverine
was lord of the vampires?

11:31.893 --> 11:34.177
Mm, do you remember what ifs, Mike?

11:34.229 --> 11:35.895
Oh, man, loved what ifs.

11:35.930 --> 11:37.930
These were real popular back in the day.

11:37.982 --> 11:40.733
<i>But I think what if has kind of,</i>

11:40.769 --> 11:42.485
you know, gone the way of the dinosaur.

11:42.520 --> 11:44.320
Really, you don't hear much about it.

11:44.355 --> 11:47.273
But I got a special place
in my heart for the what ifs.

11:47.325 --> 11:49.442
<i>What if was Marvel's fantasy book.</i>

11:49.494 --> 11:51.661
You know, battling it
out with our imaginations,

11:51.696 --> 11:54.280
asking us the important questions.

11:54.332 --> 11:56.666
<i>What if Wolverine had killed the Hulk?</i>

11:56.701 --> 11:58.367
What if the Hulk had
Bruce Banner's brain?

11:58.420 --> 11:59.669
Oh.

11:59.704 --> 12:01.204
I mean, it was just a great series.

12:01.256 --> 12:02.672
But generally, people were like,

12:02.707 --> 12:05.007
"well, that's... that's
not a real comic.

12:05.043 --> 12:06.375
<i>That's what if," which is ironic,</i>

12:06.428 --> 12:08.344
'cause the stuff that they were like,

12:08.379 --> 12:09.462
"this is a real comic where the Hulk

12:09.514 --> 12:10.930
didn't get killed by Wolverine,"

12:10.965 --> 12:11.931
it's like, "no, that's fake too."

12:11.966 --> 12:14.934
[Laughter]

12:14.969 --> 12:16.185
One of my favorite ones,

12:16.221 --> 12:17.970
which actually came to pass, though,

12:18.022 --> 12:19.522
<i>was, what if Spider-Man
joined the Fantastic Four?</i>

12:19.557 --> 12:20.857
<i>Did you have a favorite what if issue?</i>

12:20.892 --> 12:22.525
<i>I liked the what if the Vision</i>

12:22.560 --> 12:23.976
<i>had destroyed the Avengers?</i>

12:24.028 --> 12:25.812
That's one of my all-time favorites.

12:25.864 --> 12:27.196
<i>What was your favorite what if?</i>

12:27.232 --> 12:28.731
- I never read one.
- Oh, you never...

12:28.783 --> 12:30.149
- You were never into these?
- I never read one, no.

12:30.201 --> 12:31.984
- No. Were they all this serious?
- Oh, yeah.

12:32.036 --> 12:33.870
Where it's like, "what if
so-and-so killed so-and-so?"

12:33.905 --> 12:35.705
Think about it. Comics
can go anywhere.

12:35.740 --> 12:38.958
The only thing they can't do
is really kill their characters.

12:38.993 --> 12:40.376
So the only way you can really do it,

12:40.411 --> 12:41.794
the only way you can tell that story,

12:41.830 --> 12:42.829
<i>is in a what if.</i>

12:42.881 --> 12:44.497
Come on, man.

12:44.549 --> 12:46.415
I'd be like, "what if I
cared about any of this?"

12:46.468 --> 12:48.468
[Laughter]

12:49.036 --> 12:50.585
You're looking to sell these today?

12:50.621 --> 12:51.920
- Yes.
- How come?

12:51.955 --> 12:54.623
Well, I am looking to raise money

12:54.675 --> 12:57.042
to get a video game console
for a local community center,

12:57.094 --> 12:58.677
so the kids can have something to do

12:58.712 --> 12:59.856
and not be out in the street,

12:59.856 --> 13:01.296
getting into who knows
what kind of trouble.

13:01.296 --> 13:03.348
So keep them busy, give
them something to do,

13:03.384 --> 13:04.716
- All right.
- You know?

13:04.768 --> 13:05.967
I mean, did you look up any of the prices

13:06.020 --> 13:07.469
before you got here today?

13:07.521 --> 13:08.470
'Cause you're probably
not looking at...

13:08.522 --> 13:10.389
like, at a Playstation 4

13:10.441 --> 13:12.391
- or an Xbox.
- Definitely not.

13:12.443 --> 13:14.393
You're probably looking
at a... like, at a pong.

13:14.445 --> 13:16.228
- 2600?
- 2600, yeah.

13:16.280 --> 13:17.479
[Laughter]

13:17.531 --> 13:18.480
Those little tiger handhelds.

13:18.532 --> 13:19.948
Yeah.

13:19.983 --> 13:22.367
I mean, what were you
looking to get today?

13:22.403 --> 13:23.902
Well, I was hoping for at least 50.

13:23.954 --> 13:25.370
- Wow.
- Yeah.

13:25.406 --> 13:27.072
Um...

13:27.124 --> 13:29.074
I don't think I could go
that high for these issues.

13:29.126 --> 13:30.409
I mean, it's a great cause,

13:30.461 --> 13:33.795
and because it is a good cause, um...

13:33.831 --> 13:35.414
I could do 25.

13:35.466 --> 13:36.998
You wouldn't go 30?

13:37.051 --> 13:39.251
I could do 28. That's it.

13:39.303 --> 13:40.719
- Oof.
- 28.

13:40.754 --> 13:41.803
All right, sounds good. Sounds good.

13:41.839 --> 13:43.672
- 28?
- 28 sounds good.

13:43.724 --> 13:45.724
Whatever helps, whatever helps.

13:48.812 --> 13:50.178
$28, man.

13:50.230 --> 13:51.646
- All right.
- Thank you.

13:51.682 --> 13:53.815
- Thank you. All right, guys.
- Good luck.

13:53.851 --> 13:55.567
You know what?

13:55.602 --> 13:57.486
<i>They should tap us to be the
writers of what if, right?</i>

13:57.521 --> 13:58.737
That's all we do all day, like you said.

13:58.772 --> 14:00.188
Marvel comes to you.

14:00.240 --> 14:01.773
The editor says, "Ming,
what do you got for me?

14:01.825 --> 14:04.076
<i>First issue, what if relaunch."</i>

14:04.111 --> 14:05.410
Me and Mike on a deserted island.

14:05.446 --> 14:08.697
[Laughter]

14:13.120 --> 14:15.253
Yo, yo, yo, yo. All right, y'all.

14:15.289 --> 14:17.005
Microphone check, one, two.

14:17.040 --> 14:19.541
Let's do this.

14:19.593 --> 14:21.626
First rap battle the stash has ever had.

14:21.678 --> 14:23.011
Yes.

14:23.046 --> 14:26.098
How do you get to rap battle with DMC?

14:26.133 --> 14:27.766
Like, what world is this possible?

14:27.801 --> 14:29.101
Why you?

14:29.136 --> 14:30.685
I have no idea how this happened.

14:30.721 --> 14:32.304
Well, you can't back out, right?

14:32.356 --> 14:34.106
No, I can't back out,
but I'm sitting here...

14:34.141 --> 14:35.557
I was like, is this really happening?

14:35.609 --> 14:37.225
It's just... it's so crazy to me

14:37.277 --> 14:39.194
that all those years I've
been listening to run-DMC,

14:39.229 --> 14:41.863
and whenever they talk about a sucker mc,

14:41.899 --> 14:44.116
like, it's you. [Laughter]

14:44.151 --> 14:45.784
You are who they've been singing about.

14:45.819 --> 14:47.536
Like, you would think
MC meant Ming Chen.

14:47.571 --> 14:49.704
[Laughter]

14:49.740 --> 14:51.239
All right, let's do this the right way.

14:51.291 --> 14:53.041
Can somebody do the intro?

14:53.076 --> 14:54.826
On this side,

14:54.878 --> 14:57.913
you have the pioneer of an entire genre,

14:57.965 --> 15:00.749
one of the most legendary
hip-hop groups of all time,

15:00.801 --> 15:03.885
if not the all-time, run-DMC.

15:03.921 --> 15:06.588
Darryl "DMC" Mcdaniels,

15:06.640 --> 15:07.973
straight out of Hollis.

15:08.008 --> 15:10.509
[Both imitating crowd roaring]

15:10.561 --> 15:13.261
And straight out of his
condo over in Shrewsbury,

15:13.313 --> 15:15.730
because his wife let him
leave the house today,

15:15.766 --> 15:17.349
Ming Chen.

15:17.401 --> 15:18.683
I'm ready when you are, man.

15:18.735 --> 15:20.068
I had this memorized,

15:20.103 --> 15:21.903
but I want to get it smooth, so...

15:21.939 --> 15:23.522
All right, whatever it takes
for you to get the verse out.

15:23.574 --> 15:25.190
All right, all right, here we go.

15:25.242 --> 15:27.692
♪ Yo, what up, DMC? I
give your rhymes props ♪

15:27.744 --> 15:30.362
♪ Gonna take more than that
to sell your book in our shop ♪

15:30.414 --> 15:32.414
- ♪ Is your comic story tight? ♪
- Yes.

15:32.449 --> 15:34.249
♪ Or will fanboys flee? ♪

15:34.284 --> 15:36.084
♪ Do you have what it takes
to be the next Stan Lee? ♪

15:36.119 --> 15:37.452
- Yes.
- ♪ Think rap critics tough? ♪

15:37.504 --> 15:39.588
♪ Well, you haven't met my crew ♪

15:39.623 --> 15:42.207
♪ You ain't in Hollis, queens,
you in the stash now, foo' ♪

15:42.259 --> 15:44.759
- [Laughter]
- ♪ This my man flanny flan ♪

15:44.795 --> 15:46.678
♪ He been reading all his life ♪

15:46.713 --> 15:49.464
♪ But peeps are really shocked
that he really has a wife ♪

15:49.516 --> 15:51.016
♪ This my man Mike Z ♪

15:51.051 --> 15:52.601
♪ He's the comics knowledge guy ♪

15:52.636 --> 15:53.935
I see.

15:53.971 --> 15:55.437
♪ Just please please make sure ♪

15:55.472 --> 15:56.805
♪ That your book don't make him cry ♪

15:56.857 --> 15:59.474
[Laughter]

15:59.526 --> 16:00.725
♪ And my man biggie Bry ♪

16:00.777 --> 16:02.277
♪ He's the fourth fat boy ♪

16:02.312 --> 16:03.728
♪ Scream, "all you can eat" ♪

16:03.780 --> 16:05.480
♪ And he'll always be your boy ♪

16:05.532 --> 16:06.565
[Laughs]

16:06.617 --> 16:07.782
♪ That just leaves me ♪

16:07.818 --> 16:09.067
♪ To be down with the king ♪

16:09.119 --> 16:10.285
♪ But to sell your four colors ♪

16:10.320 --> 16:11.870
♪ Got to be down with the Ming ♪

16:11.905 --> 16:12.871
Ah.

16:12.906 --> 16:13.989
♪ And so now we out ♪

16:14.041 --> 16:15.874
♪ Me and my four-man crew ♪

16:15.909 --> 16:19.160
♪ And I hand over the mic,
and I throw it back to you ♪

16:19.213 --> 16:20.328
- All right.
- Yeah, yeah?

16:20.380 --> 16:21.997
- Okay.
- All right?

16:22.049 --> 16:23.164
- [Sporadic applause]
- That was... that was...

16:23.217 --> 16:24.165
I crapped my pants.

16:24.218 --> 16:26.585
[Laughter]

16:26.637 --> 16:29.421
♪ Who is the best? That's
what they are debatin' ♪

16:29.473 --> 16:31.473
♪ It's me, DMC ♪

16:31.508 --> 16:34.726
♪ And beatin' your punk ass
ain't a mother [Bleep] thing ♪

16:36.257 --> 16:37.473
I got to be honest with you,

16:37.509 --> 16:39.579
and I even want to go on the record now.

16:39.579 --> 16:41.894
I have never had more respect for you

16:42.968 --> 16:44.517
than that moment when you stepped up

16:44.553 --> 16:48.638
to the plate and you went
nose-to-nose with DMC.

16:48.690 --> 16:51.141
And you... I mean, that
took a lot of cojones, yo.

16:51.193 --> 16:52.559
I'm sorry.

16:52.611 --> 16:54.310
I noticed a pig going flying by.

16:54.362 --> 16:56.229
[Laughter]

16:56.281 --> 16:58.148
First thing I want to say about

16:58.200 --> 16:59.732
all of these wannabe rappers

16:59.784 --> 17:02.068
that exist in the world today,

17:02.120 --> 17:05.405
you know, I don't really
waste my time battling them

17:05.457 --> 17:07.240
'cause they're a waste of my...

17:07.291 --> 17:08.875
Precious energy.

17:08.910 --> 17:10.993
So instead of just going at you,

17:11.046 --> 17:13.246
I'm go about go ahead at all of you

17:13.298 --> 17:15.165
who think you can come

17:15.217 --> 17:16.415
at the king.

17:16.468 --> 17:19.002
Just want to ask you this.

17:19.054 --> 17:22.005
♪ Who is the best? That's
what they are debatin' ♪

17:22.057 --> 17:23.640
♪ While they are beef in' ♪

17:23.675 --> 17:24.924
♪ I am beatin' down Satan ♪

17:24.976 --> 17:26.425
♪ Went to the gates of hell ♪

17:26.478 --> 17:28.060
♪ And I kicked the [Bleep] gates in ♪

17:28.096 --> 17:29.312
♪ Said he was coming to see me ♪

17:29.347 --> 17:30.680
♪ I was standing there waiting ♪

17:30.732 --> 17:32.065
♪ I waited 40 days ♪

17:32.100 --> 17:33.600
♪ And for 40 nights ♪

17:33.652 --> 17:36.436
♪ I killed 40 mcs
and I rocked 40 mics ♪

17:36.488 --> 17:38.905
♪ Punk-ass Satan, he never showed up ♪

17:38.940 --> 17:42.242
♪ So I shut down hell and
I closed the gates up ♪

17:42.277 --> 17:44.994
♪ All the demons were
screamin' DMC must die ♪

17:45.030 --> 17:48.097
♪ 'Cause I raise hell and
I'm still on the rise ♪

17:48.133 --> 17:50.783
♪ High in the sky, where
the angels all fly ♪

17:50.835 --> 17:53.620
♪ For heavy D, JMJ, and left eye ♪

17:53.672 --> 17:56.422
♪ It's me, DMC it's easy being king ♪

17:56.458 --> 17:59.709
♪ And beatin' your punk ass
ain't a mother[Bleep] thing ♪

17:59.761 --> 18:02.178
[Laughter]

18:02.214 --> 18:05.265
- [Applause]
- All right. All right.

18:05.300 --> 18:07.217
All right, that was good.

18:07.269 --> 18:08.685
Give me that chain.

18:08.720 --> 18:10.470
- [Laughter]
- I think you earned it.

18:10.522 --> 18:12.021
I think you earned it.

18:12.057 --> 18:14.190
Maybe I lost, but at
least I lost to the best.

18:14.226 --> 18:15.391
You stood up.

18:15.443 --> 18:16.693
You come correct, as they say.

18:16.728 --> 18:18.561
And he respects you now, I bet.

18:18.613 --> 18:19.562
Ooh.

18:19.614 --> 18:20.613
[Laughter]

18:20.649 --> 18:21.648
I don't know.

18:21.700 --> 18:23.533
[Laughter]

18:23.568 --> 18:25.702
Man, like, this sounds like a day

18:25.737 --> 18:27.070
that I actually missed.

18:27.122 --> 18:28.371
Generally speaking,

18:28.406 --> 18:29.872
the adventures that happen around here,

18:29.908 --> 18:31.741
I'm happy to hear you guys tell me about.

18:31.793 --> 18:33.710
But this sounds like a day
I actually would have liked

18:33.745 --> 18:34.911
to have been there, man.

18:34.963 --> 18:37.297
Like, meeting DMC is a cool thing.

18:37.332 --> 18:38.748
Well, hold on.

18:38.800 --> 18:41.417
I know what a big run-DMC fan you are.

18:41.469 --> 18:43.503
I felt really bad that
you weren't there that day,

18:43.555 --> 18:46.306
so planned a little surprise for you, so...

18:46.341 --> 18:47.590
No.

18:47.642 --> 18:49.425
- Stepping up to the mic...
- No!

18:49.477 --> 18:51.144
- The king of rock...
- No!

18:51.179 --> 18:53.396
Mr. DMC himself, Darryl Mcdaniels.

18:53.431 --> 18:55.148
No!

18:55.183 --> 18:56.516
[Laughter]

18:56.568 --> 18:57.517
Oh, my lord.

18:57.569 --> 18:58.651
How are you, man?

18:58.687 --> 19:01.187
Oh, lord.

19:01.239 --> 19:02.689
Oh! [Laughter]

19:02.741 --> 19:04.073
'Cause I know you're the only one

19:04.109 --> 19:06.109
that cared enough to bring him back. Sir.

19:06.161 --> 19:07.660
Hey, what's up, Kev?

19:07.696 --> 19:11.864
Sir, you are absolutely,
have been for 30 years,

19:11.916 --> 19:13.283
one of my biggest heroes.

19:13.335 --> 19:15.168
And one of the things I loved so much

19:15.203 --> 19:16.586
about run-DMC,

19:16.621 --> 19:18.288
still do to this day,

19:18.340 --> 19:21.257
is the declarative "we know who we are."

19:21.293 --> 19:23.009
At age 14,

19:23.044 --> 19:25.094
that was so important
to hear somebody be like,

19:25.130 --> 19:27.347
"I'm the king of rock,
there is none higher."

19:27.382 --> 19:29.432
And you would sit there and be
like, "why can they say that?"

19:29.467 --> 19:32.018
And by the end of the
song, you believed them.

19:32.053 --> 19:35.355
And it was just that kind
of, like, self-assurance, man.

19:35.390 --> 19:37.273
Like, that kind of self-esteem,

19:37.309 --> 19:39.275
like, translated over to me.

19:39.311 --> 19:41.694
<i>And by the time I was ready to make clerks,</i>

19:41.730 --> 19:43.980
it was people like you who did it first.

19:44.032 --> 19:47.483
So, like, you are absolutely
one of my biggest heroes.

19:47.535 --> 19:49.485
Well, thank you, man. I mean, wow.

19:49.537 --> 19:51.120
You know, truth be told,

19:51.156 --> 19:53.406
we didn't want to be
celebrities to the audience.

19:53.458 --> 19:55.241
I think that's the...

19:55.293 --> 19:57.827
you know, people always say,
"run-DMC, they're pioneers,

19:57.879 --> 19:59.462
they're legends," we this and that.

19:59.497 --> 20:02.298
I think one of the most
important things that we did,

20:02.334 --> 20:05.802
when you saw run, d, and
Jay, you saw yourself.

20:05.837 --> 20:07.086
Yes.

20:07.138 --> 20:08.504
When we came into show business,

20:08.556 --> 20:10.923
we said, "why do we
got to change who we are

20:10.975 --> 20:13.393
just to be onstage or be
in front of the camera?"

20:13.428 --> 20:15.645
So when we stepped in front of the world,

20:15.680 --> 20:18.648
kids like you, white,
black, Puerto Rican, Asian,

20:18.683 --> 20:21.818
didn't see something
that they could not be.

20:21.853 --> 20:23.069
Yes.

20:23.104 --> 20:24.604
And they saw themselves. Whoa.

20:24.656 --> 20:25.905
All right, man, so I understand

20:25.940 --> 20:27.857
the king of rock was forced

20:27.909 --> 20:30.576
into some sort of rap
battle with the king of not.

20:30.612 --> 20:32.161
- Yeah, yeah. Well, yeah.
- [Laughter]

20:32.197 --> 20:34.030
We went verse for verse, line for line.

20:34.082 --> 20:36.165
All I got to say to you is this:

20:36.201 --> 20:37.250
Practice.

20:37.285 --> 20:38.323
[Laughter]

20:39.710 --> 20:41.180
Oh! That's all the time we got.

20:41.180 --> 20:42.704
We got to hip-op out of here, man.

20:42.704 --> 20:44.389
For Comic Book Men,
I'm your host Kevin Smith.

20:44.389 --> 20:45.833
- Bryan Johnson.
- Walt Flanagan.

20:45.833 --> 20:46.908
Darryl Mcdaniel.

20:46.908 --> 20:48.239
- Mike Zapcic.
- Ming Chen.

20:48.410 --> 20:50.455
Remember kids, it's like that, yo.

